Returns from the [[2000 United States census|2010 census]] show that 491 people resided in the CDP that year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/cf/1.0/en/place/Spanish%20Valley%20CDP,%20Utah/ALL|title=American FactFinder - Community Facts|publisher=United States Census Bureau|date=|website=factfinder.census.gov|language=en|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213235219/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/cf/1.0/en/place/Spanish%20Valley%20CDP,%20Utah/ALL|archive-date=2020-02-13|url-status=dead|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> Estimates from the 2017 [[American Community Survey]] indicated that the area had a population of 594. American Community Survey data from between 2013 and 2017 indicates that the area had 185 housing units.

American Community Survey data from 2013 to 2017 indicated the area's median age in 2017 was 30.2 years, with a [[margin of error]] of 17.3 years. Seven years prior, the census showed that this figure was 54.9 years, with a margin of error of 8.3 years.

Five-year survey estimates from 2013 to 2017 showed that 96% of the residents (573 people) were [[White people|White]]; the other 4% (21 people) were [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]].

The area's median income during the 2013 to 2017 time period is not available, but survey estimates showed that 11.9% of the population lived below the [[Poverty thresholds (United States Census Bureau)|poverty level]] during that time.

